<DocsLayout title="AI Scoring" description="LeadEcho's 4-stage AI scoring pipeline — rules filter, semantic matching, intent classification, lead qualification.">
  <h1>AI Scoring Pipeline</h1>

  <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
    Every post collected from monitored platforms passes through a four-stage scoring pipeline.
    Each stage either eliminates noise or adds signal, producing a relevance score and intent
    classification that determines where the post lands in the inbox.
  </p>

  <pre><code>Incoming post
     │
     ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Stage 1: Rules Filter               │  Fast — no AI calls
│  Rejects spam, too-short content     │
└─────────────────┬────────────────────┘
                  │ pass
                  ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Stage 2: Semantic Matching          │  Voyage AI embeddings
│  Cosine similarity vs pain profiles  │
└─────────────────┬────────────────────┘
                  │ score ≥ 0.40 (or no profiles)
                  ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Stage 3: Intent Classification      │  LLM call (GLM / OpenAI)
│  intent + conversion_probability     │
│  + relevance_score (0–10)            │
│  + awareness_level                   │
└─────────────────┬────────────────────┘
                  │
                  ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Stage 4: Lead Qualification         │  Local logic
│  Auto-creates lead if score ≥ 7.0   │
│  + buy_signal / recommendation_ask   │
└──────────────────────────────────────┘</code></pre>

  <h2>Stage 1 — Rules Filter</h2>

  <p>The rules filter is a cheap, synchronous pass that runs before any API call:</p>

  <h3>Rejection Criteria</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Content length under <strong>50 characters</strong> — too short to contain meaningful signal.</li>
    <li>Spam keyword match — any of the following phrases trigger immediate rejection:</li>
  </ul>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Spam Phrase</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>click here to win</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>free money</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>limited time offer</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>act now</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>buy followers</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>crypto airdrop</code></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>Posts rejected at Stage 1 are dropped silently — they never reach the database.</p>

  <h2>Stage 2 — Semantic Matching</h2>

  <p>
    If at least one pain-point profile exists and a <code>VOYAGE_API_KEY</code> is configured,
    Stage 2 embeds the incoming post and computes cosine similarity against stored profile embeddings.
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Parameter</th>
        <th>Value</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Embedding model</td>
        <td><code>voyage-3-lite</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Vector dimensions</td>
        <td>1024</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Index type</td>
        <td>HNSW (pgvector)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Distance function</td>
        <td>Cosine similarity</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Minimum threshold</td>
        <td>0.40</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Content truncation</td>
        <td>2000 chars (cost control)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Stage 2 Skip Conditions</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>No pain-point profiles configured for the workspace.</li>
    <li><code>VOYAGE_API_KEY</code> not set (falls back to keyword-only matching).</li>
  </ul>

  <p>When Stage 2 is skipped, all posts that passed Stage 1 proceed to Stage 3.</p>

  <h2>Stage 3 — Intent Classification</h2>

  <p>
    An LLM call classifies the post's intent and assigns numerical scores.
    Temperature is kept at <strong>0.1</strong> to produce consistent, deterministic results.
  </p>

  <h3>Provider Selection</h3>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Provider</th>
        <th>Model</th>
        <th>Priority</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Zhipu AI (GLM)</td>
        <td><code>glm-4.5-flash</code></td>
        <td>1st — preferred</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>OpenAI</td>
        <td><code>gpt-4o-mini</code></td>
        <td>2nd — fallback</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Intent Categories</h3>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Intent</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Example</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>buy_signal</code></td>
        <td>Actively looking to purchase or switch tools</td>
        <td>"Looking for a better CRM, budget is $200/mo"</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>recommendation_ask</code></td>
        <td>Asking for tool recommendations</td>
        <td>"What do you use for client reporting?"</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>complaint</code></td>
        <td>Expressing frustration with a current solution</td>
        <td>"Salesforce is overkill for a 3-person team"</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>comparison</code></td>
        <td>Comparing options</td>
        <td>"HubSpot vs Pipedrive for agencies?"</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>general</code></td>
        <td>Informational, no clear purchase intent</td>
        <td>"Interesting article about CRM adoption"</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Awareness Level</h3>

  <p>
    In addition to intent, Stage 3 now classifies the buyer's <strong>awareness level</strong> — how far
    along they are in the buying journey. This drives reply template selection in
    <a href="/docs/smart-reply-drafting">Smart Reply Drafting</a> and appears as color-coded badges in the inbox.
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Level</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>problem_aware</code></td>
        <td>Knows they have a problem but hasn't started looking for solutions</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>solution_aware</code></td>
        <td>Actively researching solution categories</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>product_aware</code></td>
        <td>Comparing specific products by name</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>purchase_ready</code></td>
        <td>Ready to buy — mentions budget, timeline, or specific requirements</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>LLM Output Schema</h3>

  <pre><code>&#123;
  "intent": "buy_signal",
  "conversion_probability": 0.82,
  "relevance_score": 8.5,
  "reasoning": "Author explicitly states budget and urgency...",
  "awareness_level": "purchase_ready"
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>Stage 4 — Lead Qualification</h2>

  <p>Stage 4 is synchronous local logic — no additional API calls.</p>

  <h3>Auto-Qualification Criteria</h3>

  <p>A lead is automatically created when <strong>all</strong> of the following are true:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><code>relevance_score</code> ≥ <strong>7.0</strong></li>
    <li><code>intent</code> is one of: <code>buy_signal</code>, <code>recommendation_ask</code>, <code>complaint</code></li>
  </ul>

  <p>Auto-qualified leads receive the tag <code>auto-qualified</code> and appear immediately in the Leads section.
  Duplicate leads (same post URL already seen) are silently skipped.</p>

  <h2>Smart Inbox Tiers</h2>

  <p>All scored posts are routed into the Smart Inbox based on their final score:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Tier</th>
        <th>Score Range</th>
        <th>Intents</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Leads Ready</td>
        <td>≥ 7.0</td>
        <td>buy_signal, recommendation_ask, complaint</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Worth Watching</td>
        <td>4.0 – 6.9</td>
        <td>Any</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Informational</td>
        <td>&lt; 4.0</td>
        <td>general, comparison</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Cost Estimates</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Component</th>
        <th>Cost per 1,000 posts</th>
        <th>Monthly (2,000 posts)</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>GPT-4o-mini scoring</td>
        <td>~$0.025</td>
        <td>~$0.05</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Voyage AI embeddings</td>
        <td>~$0.001</td>
        <td>~$0.002</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>GLM-4.5-flash (alternative)</td>
        <td>~$0.010</td>
        <td>~$0.02</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <blockquote>
    <p>
      Costs scale linearly with post volume. The 2,000 post/month estimate is typical for
      monitoring 3–5 keywords across 4 platforms. Heavy usage (20+ keywords) may reach $1–5/month.
    </p>
  </blockquote>
</DocsLayout>
